-ver="1" data-id="1666204999561"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 870px !important; height: 160px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 435px 80px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 870px !important; height: 160px !important;"><canvas class="lt-highlighter__canvas" width="59" height="25" style="display: none; top: 100px !important; left: 287px !important;"></canvas></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-713018" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;">If you experience wrist pain when lifting, you might have been lifting without proper form and technique. Wrists are not built to take a lot of stress, but they have a special power. They can serve as a conduit for the stress to pass through from your hands to your arms and the rest of your body. Proper form dictates that you must keep your wrists straight to allow the stress to pass through as it should. Bend them sideways and your wrists start taking on some of the stress because there’s no free flow anymore. Before long, your wrists will be in pain and you’ll be left wondering why.</p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;"><br></p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;">So make sure to keep your wrists in proper form for whatever exercise you’re doing to avoid any wrist injury from lifting. This is the first and most important step.</p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;"></p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;"></p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;"></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1667226576107" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1667226576107"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 870px !important; height: 53.8333px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 435px 26.9167px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 870px !important; height: 53.8333px !important;"><canvas class="lt-highlighter__canvas" width="216" height="40" style="display: none; top: 2px !important; left: 455px !important;"></canvas></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-161493" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Too much weight</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1667226586366" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1667226586366"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 870px !important; height: 160px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 435px 80px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 870px !important; height: 160px !important;"><canvas class="lt-highlighter__canvas" width="59" height="25" style="display: none; top: 100px !important; left: 287px !important;"></canvas></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-713018" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;">Over lifting is another reason you might be experiencing wrist pain from lifting weights. It’s normal to be so eager to progress that you just pile on the weights as fast as you can. That can be dangerous, however, because eagerness does not always mean readiness.</p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;"><br></p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;">As you lift, your whole body develops together. Balance is one thing beginners are advised about when they start. You don’t want to build up your chest and leave your legs behind because you might become very strong with legs that can’t carry your weight. This applies to your wrists as well.</p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;"><br></p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;">That your biceps and triceps are strong enough to lift heavy weights doesn’t mean your wrist is ready for that. So, especially if you’re a beginner, take it easy with the weights. Start small and slowly but steadily work your way up. Haste makes waste.</p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;"></p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;"></p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;"></p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;"></p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;"></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1667226623550" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1667226623550"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 870px !important; height: 53.8333px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 435px 26.9167px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 870px !important; height: 53.8333px !important;"><canvas class="lt-highlighter__canvas" width="216" height="40" style="display: none; top: 2px !important; left: 455px !important;"></canvas></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-161493" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Too much work</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1667226626356" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1667226626356"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 870px !important; height: 160px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 435px 80px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 870px !important; height: 160px !important;"><canvas class="lt-highlighter__canvas" width="59" height="25" style="display: none; top: 100px !important; left: 287px !important;"></canvas></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-713018" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;">If you’re not piling on the weights, another thing you might be doing wrong out of eagerness is piling on the reps and rounds. Again, the enthusiasm is good, but overworking yourself will only pull you backwards. Overuse of anything will eventually wear it out, and your wrists are no different.</p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;"><br></p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;">One of the most important but often neglected parts of fitness is recovery. No matter how hard you work, you are still human and your body needs rest. There are several studies that have shown time and time again how important rest is yet most people continue to ignore it. Recovery allows your body to reset, to self heal if there are any strains. Skipping your rest will prevent your body from refreshing itself and expose you to injuries that might be brewing up without your knowledge.</p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;"><br></p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;">Often, wrist injuries are not immediately apparent and we just tough it out and keep going. The stress builds up without your knowledge until it’s too much to hide, then it bursts out in your face and leaves you with sore wrists from lifting. So give your wrists time to rest. Space out your reps and rounds such that your body is well taken care of.</p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;"></p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;"></p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;"></p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;"></p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;"></p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;"></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1666254290035" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1666254290035" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-cente